    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In chemistry, an organic compound in which one or more hydroxyl functional groups (-OH) are bound to a carbon atom; the carbon center should be saturated, having single bonds to three other atoms.</Note_Text>
